cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to transform modern English to Shakespearean English. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses neural models and embeddings, which are common techniques in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also mentions the use of pointers, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of end-to-end trainable neural models, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category cs.DL (Deep Learning).
